{
  "texts": [
    "But implementation and enforcement promise to be an uphill battle, fought tooth and nail by the major platforms at every step.",
    "In response to this predicament, some researchers have argued that we should build recommender systems that can be layered on top of the existing platform ecosystem, as a kind of \"middleware\" (Fukuyama, 2021).",
    "The idea is that personal recommender systems could filter and rank the content on platforms without themselves being controlled by those platforms.",
    "While this is an attractive proposal, little progress has yet been made, for some fairly fundamental reasons.",
    "Existing recommender systems rely on ML techniques, like deep learning, which require vast amounts of behavioral data to function."
  ]
}